courses.description: - Continuation of Accounting 200. Topics included are partnerships and corporations with special emphasis on managerial accounting. Prerequisite: ACCT 200.

- Course is designed for non-accounting majors. Coverage includes the application of accounting concepts and techniques to managerial problems of planning, control land decision-making. Prerequisite: ACCT 200.
- Introduction to the study of payroll, property, and sales tax. Prerequisite: ACCT 200.
- Federal income tax relating to individuals and partnerships. Prerequisite: ACCT 200.
- This is an introductory course dealing with the economic importance of the agribusiness community and the potential for employment with the agribusiness industry.
- Variable instructional topics in the field of agriculture. Repeatable with varied content.
General principles of the livestock industry and their relationship to mankind.
Principles of feeding livestock including the functions of the digestive system, nutrient requirements, nutrient characteristics, and sources utilized in the formulation of balanced rations.
- (3 credits) Principles of range management which include plant identifications, range evaluation, and range improvement.
